              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7131794198451475183">Sears history of the penninsula campaign is extremely readable and insightful. It gives interesting insight of the peculiar problems of communication problems and fog of war that impacted these battles in that era. It also shows these generals still learning to lead. Sears is one of the better writers of battles in this era. He writes in a way that explains complicated maneuvers . Highly recommend this book.</span>

