      var newTip = new Tip($('bookCover_782930'), "\n\n  <h2><a class=\"readable bookTitle\" href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/782930.Gettysburg_The_First_Day?from_choice=false&amp;from_home_module=false\">Gettysburg--The First Day<\/a><\/h2>\n\n      <div>\n        by <a class=\"authorName\" href=\"/author/show/411345.Harry_W_Pfanz?a=9&amp;origin=related_works\">Harry W. Pfanz<\/a>\n      <\/div>\n\n          <div class=\"smallText uitext darkGreyText\">\n            <span class=\"minirating\"><span class=\"stars staticStars notranslate\"><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p10\"><\/span><span size=\"12x12\" class=\"staticStar p3\"><\/span><\/span> 4.33 avg rating &mdash; 425 ratings<\/span>            &mdash; published 2001\n          <\/div>\n\n    <div class=\"addBookTipDescription\">\n      \n<span id=\"freeTextContainer5460157508440776284\">For good reason, the second and third days of the Battle of Gettysburg have received the lion&apos;s share of attention from historians. With this book, however, the critical first day&apos;s fighting finally receives its due. After sketching the background of<\/span>\n  <span id=\"freeText5460157508440776284\" style=\"display:none\">For good reason, the second and third days of the Battle of Gettysburg have received the lion\'s share of attention from historians. With this book, however, the critical first day\'s fighting finally receives its due. After sketching the background of the Gettysburg campaign and recounting the events immediately preceding the battle, Harry Pfanz offers a detailed tactical description of events of the first day. He describes the engagements in McPherson Woods, at the Railroad Cuts, on Oak Ridge, on Seminary Ridge, and at Blocher\'s Knoll, as well as the retreat of Union forces through Gettysburg and the Federal rally on Ce